org.mitre.provenance.workflowengine.activity

Class Activity

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.mitre.provenance.workflowengine.activity.Activity
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GenericActivity, PLUSObjectEmittingActivity

    public class Activity
extends Object
    This object models a particular activity in a Workflow. Activities are considered black-box by default; they have only inputs, outputs, and transitions. There are two types of transitions; "transitions" are arcs out of the activity going elsewhere. "introductions" are arcs into the activity coming from elsewhere. In this sense, they can be thought of as a graph or form of doubly linked list.
    Author:
    DMALLEN

      • getRequiredInputNames

        public Hashtable<String,Class<?>> getRequiredInputNames()
        Subclass this method and have it return a the variables that are needed in order for this activity to run properly. If your activity relies on having particular inputs with particular names, this is the way to tell your caller about those requirements. This particular method returns an empty hash.
        Returns:
        a list of input variable names mapped to Class objects describing the types needed.

      • checkInputTypes

        public void checkInputTypes(Hashtable<String,PLUSObject> inputs)
                     throws ActivityException
        Given a list of inputs, this method will determine whether or not the activities requirements have been met. If all of the necessary inputs are present, it will do nothing.
        Parameters:
        inputs - the inputs to the activity execution.
        Throws:
        ActivityException - if some required input is missing, or of the wrong type.s

      • hasOutput

        public boolean hasOutput(String name)
        Determines whether this activity will output a given variable name. This applies both for registered outputs, and "parroted" outputs.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the variable you're interested in
        Returns:
        true if the activity will output that variable, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        parrotOutput(String, PLUSObject), registerOutput(String, Metadata)

      • parrotOutput

        public void parrotOutput(String varName,
                         PLUSObject value)
        This method is used when you want an activity to simply emit a particular output after it has finished executing, even if it wasn't part of the input. For example, if you want the start state to emit a token, you could tell the start activity to "parrot" a particular value, which would serve as an input to your first activity.

      • execute

        public Hashtable<String,PLUSObject> execute(Hashtable<String,PLUSObject> inputVariableMappings)
                                     throws ActivityException
        Override this method to perform actual work in activities. When an activity in a workflow is executed, this method will be called.

        Subclasses should put all output variables into the hash outputMappings, which has already been created for you, and stores needed "parrot" variables.

        This method by default will create output data items with a security code of 5. The outputs will also have an uncertainty equal to 0.5

        Parameters:
        inputVariableMappings - a hashtable with keys that are the names of input paramters, and values that are specific PLUSObjects to be used for those inputs.
        Returns:
        a hashtable with keys that are the names of registered output parameters, and values that are specific PLUSObjects to be used for those outputs.
        Throws:
        ActivityException
        See Also:
        outputMappings
